What is the structure of your dataset? </br>¶

The dataset contains 113,937 loans with 81 features including (EmploymentStatus, LoanStatus, BorrowerAPR, IncomeRange, CreditGrade, Investors and many others features)</br>

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset? </br>¶

I'm most interested in figureing out what features are best for predicting the Investors for the loan.</br>

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?</br>¶

I expect that the total loan amount will have a positive effect on the Investors. I also think that the EmploymentStatus, LoanStatus, BorrowerAPR, IncomeRange, CreditGrade will also have effects on the Investors.</br>

def boxgrid(x, y, **kwargs):
    """ Quick hack for creating box plots with seaborn's PairGrid. """
    default_color = sb.color_palette()[0]
    sb.boxplot(x, y, color = default_color)

plt.figure(figsize = [10 , 10])
g = sb.PairGrid(data = df_subset, y_vars = ['BorrowerAPR', 'Investors'], 
                x_vars = categoric_vars, size = 3, aspect = 1.5)
